Installation Instructions
*************************

This release provides a precompiled binary file suitable for execution on a Linux machine. If you would prefer to compile your own version, download the source code and run the following commands:

Installation from Source
========================
* cd to the root directory of the CAFE source
* Type "make"

Optional Feature
================
If the GNU readline library is installed on your system and you wish to use it to provide a command history for CAFE, instead type the following command: "make USE_READLINE=1"


Basic Installation
==================
Copy the binary file "cafe" to somewhere on your path. /usr/local/bin is often used.